      <abstract>
        <variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>TOPIC</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                When deploying multiple virtual machines (VM), they often serve
                similar purpose. &virt-scenario; offers a way to quickly create
                a VM following one of predefined scenarios.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>INTENTION</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                This article details predefined scenarios as well as steps to
                create a VM suitable for a selected scenario.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>EFFORT</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                It takes up to 30 minutes to understand the concept of
                &virt-scenario; and create a customized VM. To learn additional
                topics, for example, how to deploy a secure VM or use
                interactive commands, you need additional time.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
      </abstract>
